sec.p:
Normally input – output data is available from experimental setup. Due to the presence of ‘measurement noise’ and ‘process noise’ the system state and output equations of the stochastic system have the following form:
(39)X·(t)=AX(t)+B2u(t)+w(t)y(t)=C2X(t)+D22u(t)+v(t)}
where v (t) is the measurement noise vector and w (t) is the process noise vector respectively. As assumed w (t) and v (t) are each zero – mean, white noise sequences in vector form, with known covariance and uncorrelated with each other. Using the inputs u (t) and outputs y (t) the future state vector X (t) can be estimated accurately by using Kalman Filter.
